dev/plans/prompts/0.7.1-EMBEDDER-UNDEFER-HANDOFF.md:7:- **Starting state**: `NoopEmbedder` returns `[1, 0, 0, ...]` (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-embedder/src/lib.rs:19-25`). `Engine.open` already records `default_embedder_identity()` (`fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3507`) using hard-coded `fathomdb-noop / 0.6.0-scaffold / 384`. `_fathomdb_embedder_profiles` profile-pins on first write and fails-closed on mismatch (`lib.rs:3515-3614`). `OpenReport` already carries `default_embedder` + `embedder_warmup_ms` (`lib.rs:548-554`). Bindings already expose `EmbedderIdentity` and the open-report fields (`fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs:356-388`, `fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:35`), but neither binding exposes a way to *supply* an embedder yet.
dev/plans/prompts/0.7.1-EMBEDDER-UNDEFER-HANDOFF.md:8:- **Campaign target**: ship a real default embedder so the `default_embedder` identity in `OpenReport` reports a real model, the engine can synthesize query/doc vectors for AC-013/AC-019 against natural-text corpora, and "default embedder = on" is the documented happy path. Caller-supplied embedders remain available; bindings expose only the *default-on/off* toggle in 0.7.1.
dev/plans/prompts/0.7.1-EMBEDDER-UNDEFER-HANDOFF.md:81:**Mandate**: carve a tightly-scoped exception to NEED-017 (`dev/needs.md:132`) and REQ-033 (`dev/requirements.md:270-274`) permitting the engine to fetch default-embedder weights on first use, gated by the caller having explicitly opted into the default embedder.
dev/plans/prompts/0.7.1-EMBEDDER-UNDEFER-HANDOFF.md:85:> **Exception (default embedder only).** When the caller opts into the default embedder by passing `use_default_embedder=true` (or by selecting it explicitly at construction), the engine MAY download the single declared default-embedder weight set from a fixed URL set on first use, cache it under the platform user-cache directory, verify by sha256, and load it. This exception is scoped to: (a) the single named default-embedder identity recorded in the workspace; (b) weight files referenced by sha256 in the published `fathomdb-embedder` crate; (c) no other model, no arbitrary URL, no user-controllable model name. Caller-supplied embedders remain caller-owned per the unchanged rule. The first-use download path SHALL emit a structured `default_embedder_download` event in `OpenReport.embedder_events` describing url + bytes + sha256 + cache-path, so the wire/disk activity is visible.
dev/plans/prompts/0.7.1-EMBEDDER-UNDEFER-HANDOFF.md:202:- `open_with_default_embedder_reports_real_identity` — `OpenReport.default_embedder.name` is the chosen model name, not `"fathomdb-noop"`.
dev/plans/prompts/0.7.1-EMBEDDER-UNDEFER-HANDOFF.md:206:- `existing_workspace_with_noop_profile_fails_closed` — a workspace previously opened with `fathomdb-noop` profile-pinned must NOT silently re-pin to BGE; it must fail with `EmbedderIdentityMismatch`. This is the existing fail-closed behavior (`lib.rs:3602-3607`) and the migration story per `ADR-0.8.0-embedder-identity-change-workflow`.
dev/plans/prompts/0.7.1-EMBEDDER-UNDEFER-HANDOFF.md:228:   the constant bump and the AC-013b RED-to-GREEN re-baseline.
