dev/plans/prompts/0.7.1-EMBEDDER-UNDEFER-HANDOFF.md:264:**Mandate**: expose the "use default embedder" toggle to Python and TS callers. Caller-supplied custom `Embedder` impls in the binding languages are **out of scope for 0.7.1** (would require new PyO3 callback bridges per Invariant 3 of ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol — that is its own multi-slice campaign). The 0.7.1 surface is binary: default-on or nothing.
dev/plans/prompts/0.7.1-EMBEDDER-UNDEFER-HANDOFF.md:268:- **Python** (`fathomdb-py`): add `use_default_embedder: bool = False` to `Engine.open(...)`. When True, the binding constructs `EmbedderChoice::Default` Rust-side. No `Embedder` Python ABC yet. Re-export `EmbedderIdentity` (already done at `fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:35`) — no change. Document in `interfaces/python.md` that custom Python embedders ship in a later release.
