dev/plans/runs/0.7.1-EU-5f-EU-7-review-20260530T130438Z.log:275:  "honesty_report": "AC-013b recall@10 does NOT meet the current 0.90 floor: 0.828 at the full real corpus (N=7667), 95% CI 0.796-0.858, well below 0.90 (gap ~0.072; the entire CI sits below the floor). AC-013 latency (p50 25 ms / p99 40 ms vs 80/300 ms) and AC-019 stress (p99 343 ms vs 405 ms bound) both PASS on the dev box. The recall gap is consistent with EU-0 3's literature expectation for real BGE under sign-bit quantization (~79-90% retention), but it is materially below EU-0's synthetic-pipeline estimate of 0.933 at K=192+mc. Three drivers, in likely order of impact: (1) production mean-centering pins the corpus mean on the FIRST 256 ingested docs -- here all bahmutov_dailylogs, a single non-representative source -- not the full-corpus mean EU-0 used; this is the documented topic-drift limitation (embedder-decision.md 3.4) and depresses centering quality for the rest of the corpus; (2) 512-token truncation (EU-5f Finding C) drops content from long cnn_dailymail articles; (3) the EU-7 query synthesis (title-or-lead-sentence) and the production engine path differ from EU-0's Python harness. Per the EU-7 mandate this slice does NOT re-pin AC013B_RECALL_FLOOR and does NOT re-word the ADR. Recommended PR-2 floor from this dev-box anchor is R - 2*sigma = 0.795, rounded down to 0.79; PR-2 should re-derive against canonical N=1M (PR-3) and, with HITL, decide whether to (a) accept a ~0.79-0.83 floor, (b) revisit mean-pin representativeness (e.g. pin on a stratified sample or re-derive after first-ingest), or (c) escalate the embedder ladder (K=256 / bge-base). The mean-pin-on-first-256 representativeness issue is itself a finding worth HITL attention beyond the floor number.",
dev/plans/runs/0.7.1-EU-5f-EU-7-review-20260530T130438Z.log:276:  "next_step_for_orchestrator": "Spawn codex reviewer on EU-5f + EU-7. AC-013 and AC-019 are GREEN (dev-box); AC-013b is honestly reported BELOW 0.90 and surfaced to HITL (not a silent pass, not a floor re-pin). Do NOT advance to EU-8 as a clean pass: route the recall RED + the mean-pin-representativeness finding to HITL / 0.7.2 PR-2 before the floor lock-flip. EU-8 (docs + v0.7.1 tag) and PR-2 (floor re-derivation) consume this anchor."
