    61	  (0.828) was a **measurement artifact** — exclude-after-top-10 plus
    62	  body-string ground truth over a corpus with ~5.6 % duplicate bodies — **not**
    63	  an engine deficiency. The corrected ANN-fidelity measurement (exclude the
    64	  query-source doc *before* top-10; dedup-by-id GT) on the real default embedder
    65	  (bge-small, N=7,667, K=192, mean-centering) is **recall@10 = 0.937 (CI
    66	  0.913–0.957, σ=0.0116)**; the full CI clears the 0.90 floor, so the floor is
    67	  **kept at 0.90, not raised**. This number is **ANN/quantization fidelity**
    68	  (how faithfully the 1-bit sign-quant index reproduces the same model's exact
    69	  f32 top-10), **not IR relevance**. The separate embedder IR-relevance ceiling
