   130	## 0.7.1 - 2026-06-01
   131	
   132	EMBEDDER-UNDEFER: the default embedder is no longer deferred. fathomdb now
   133	ships a real in-process default embedder (`BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5`, 384d, via
   134	`candle-transformers`), opt-in per binding, feeding the 0.7.0 sign-bit +
   135	f32-rerank retrieval pipeline with mean-centering. The tag was intentionally
   136	held until the 0.7.2 RELEASE-HARDENING campaign re-derived the real-corpus
   137	recall floor (`AC013B_RECALL_FLOOR`): that work found the apparent 0.828 recall
   138	"gap" was a measurement artifact, the corrected ANN-fidelity number is 0.937,
   139	and the 0.90 floor holds (see the 0.7.2 "Changed" section). `v0.7.1` is cut and
   140	published here alongside `v0.7.0`. See `dev/plans/0.7.1-implementation.md`.
   141	
   142	### Added
   143	
   144	- **Default embedder (opt-in).** `BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5` (384d) runs in
   145	  process via `candle-transformers`; WordPiece tokenization (truncated to 512
   146	  tokens) → mean-pool → L2-norm → mean-centering → sign-bit quantization →
   147	  bit-KNN (K=192) → f32 rerank → top-10. Opt in with Python
   148	  `Engine.open(path, use_default_embedder=True)` or TypeScript
   149	  `engineOpen(path, { useDefaultEmbedder: true })`; default is OFF (no embedder
   150	  configured, vector writes fail with `EmbedderNotConfigured` as before).
   151	  Caller-supplied embedders remain available in Rust; custom Python/TS embedder
   152	  bridges are deferred to 0.8.x.
   153	- **First-use weight download (visible, verified).** With the default embedder
   154	  enabled, first use downloads the pinned weight set from a fixed Hugging Face
   155	  URL set, caches it under the platform cache directory, and verifies every
   156	  file by sha256 (no trust-on-first-use). The activity is surfaced in
   157	  `OpenReport.embedder_events` (per-file url + bytes + sha256 + cache path) and
   158	  `OpenReport.embedder_download_ms`. `HF_TOKEN` is honored for token-gated
   159	  mirrors; public bge-small needs none. This is the scoped opt-in exception to
   160	  NEED-017 / REQ-033 (see `ADR-0.7.1-default-embedder-weight-fetch`).
   161	- **Mean-centering.** A per-workspace corpus-mean f32 vector is stored in
   162	  `_fathomdb_embedder_profiles.mean_vec` and subtracted before sign-bit
   163	  quantization (the f32 rerank stays un-centered). It is pinned once at the
   164	  first 256 ingested vectors and never silently recomputed.
   165	- **Bindings.** Python `use_default_embedder` / TypeScript `useDefaultEmbedder`
   166	  open flags; `OpenReport` gains `embedder_download_ms`, `embedder_events`
   167	  (typed union), `embedder_mean_centering_required`, `embedder_mean_vec_pinned`.
   168	- **Docs.** `docs/embedder.md` user guide (opt-in, first-use download, cache,
   169	  offline notes, caveats, migration).
   170	
