   182	### Fixed
   183	
   184	- **Mean-centering is now applied on the production write path.** Prior to this
   185	  release the corpus-mean pin/apply only ran via an internal test seam; the
   186	  async `engine.write` → projection path never pinned, so real ingests were
   187	  sign-quantized un-centered. The pin + re-quantize now run inside the
   188	  projection commit (serialized for cross-worker correctness), with an
   189	  open-time recovery pin for crash-before-pin workspaces.
   190	- **Embedder inputs over 512 tokens are truncated** instead of erroring. Long
   191	  documents previously failed the BGE forward pass
   192	  (`index-select invalid index 512`).
   193	- **Projection workers are fault-isolated.** A panic inside an embedder no
   194	  longer wedges the projection scheduler (`drain` could previously hang into a
   195	  scheduler timeout); the faulted batch is recorded and the worker recovers.
