 succeeded in 0ms:
     1	# Default Embedder
     2	
     3	FathomDB can embed your documents for you with a built-in, in-process embedder,
     4	so you do not have to wire up an embedding model yourself. It is **opt-in**: a
     5	fresh engine has no embedder configured and vector writes fail with
     6	`EmbedderNotConfigured` until you either enable the default embedder or supply
     7	your own (Rust only, today).
     8	
     9	> Status: the default embedder ships in 0.7.1. The real-corpus recall floor was
    10	> re-derived in the 0.7.2 hardening release: the apparent recall "gap" seen
    11	> during 0.7.1 scouting was a measurement artifact, the corrected ANN-fidelity
    12	> recall@10 is **0.937** on the reference corpus, and the 0.90 floor holds — see
    13	> [Caveats](#caveats-and-limitations).
    14	
    15	## What it is
    16	
    17	| | |
    18	|---|---|
    19	| Model | `BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5` |
    20	| Dimensions | 384 |
    21	| Runtime | `candle-transformers` BERT, pure-Rust, in process (no Python, no sidecar) |
    22	| Pipeline | WordPiece tokenization (max 512 tokens) → mean-pool → L2-normalize → mean-centering → sign-bit quantization → bit-KNN (K=192) → f32 rerank → top-10 |
    23	
    24	Documents longer than 512 tokens are truncated to the model's context window.
    25	
    26	## Enabling it
    27	
    28	The default embedder is gated behind a build feature so users who never use it
    29	pay no dependency or binary-size cost. Install the embedder-enabled
    30	distribution, then opt in at `open`.
    31	
    32	### Python
    33	
    34	```python
    35	from fathomdb import Engine
    36	
    37	engine = Engine.open("mydb.sqlite", use_default_embedder=True)
    38	report = engine.open_report()
    39	print(report.default_embedder.name)   # "fathomdb-bge-small-en-v1.5"
    40	```
    41	
    42	Install the embedder extra:
    43	
    44	```bash
    45	pip install "fathomdb[default-embedder]"
    46	```
    47	
    48	### TypeScript
    49	
    50	```ts
    51	import { engineOpen } from "fathomdb";
    52	
    53	const engine = await engineOpen("mydb.sqlite", { useDefaultEmbedder: true });
    54	console.log(engine.openReport().defaultEmbedder.name); // "fathomdb-bge-small-en-v1.5"
    55	```
    56	
    57	The embedder-enabled native binary is larger; see your platform package notes.
    58	
    59	### Default OFF
    60	
    61	If you do not pass the flag, the engine opens normally but has no embedder, and
    62	vector writes raise `EmbedderNotConfigured`. This is unchanged from earlier
    63	releases. Supplying your own custom embedder is available in the Rust API today;
    64	custom Python/TypeScript embedders are planned for a later release.
    65	
    66	## First use: weight download
    67	
    68	The model weights are **not** bundled. The first time you open an engine with
    69	the default embedder, FathomDB downloads the pinned weight files (~133 MB total)
    70	from a fixed Hugging Face URL set, caches them under your platform cache
    71	directory, and verifies every file by sha256 before loading. Subsequent opens
    72	read from the cache and do no network I/O.
    73	
    74	This first-use download is the single, narrowly-scoped exception to FathomDB's
    75	"no implicit network access" rule, and it is **visible**: the open report records
    76	what happened.
    77	
    78	```python
    79	report = engine.open_report()
    80	print(report.embedder_download_ms)   # Some(ms) on a cold cache, None when warm
    81	for ev in report.embedder_events:    # per-file url, bytes, sha256, cache path
    82	    print(ev)
    83	```
    84	
    85	Notes:
    86	
    87	- **Offline / pre-warming.** Warm the cache ahead of time (e.g. in CI or an
    88	  air-gapped build step) so the first real open does no network I/O. A cold
    89	  cache with no network will fail the open with a clear loader error rather than
    90	  hanging silently.
    91	- **`HF_TOKEN`.** If set, it is sent as a bearer token for token-gated mirrors.
    92	  The public `bge-small-en-v1.5` does not require one. No other credential
    93	  source is consulted, and the token is never persisted.
    94	- **Integrity.** A file whose sha256 does not match the pinned value is removed
    95	  and the open fails; there is no trust-on-first-use.
    96	
    97	## Mean-centering
    98	
    99	Real embeddings cluster on a narrow cone of the vector space, which hurts
   100	sign-bit quantization. FathomDB corrects for this by subtracting a per-workspace
   101	**corpus-mean vector** before the sign-bit step (the full-precision rerank stays
   102	un-centered). The mean is computed once, from the first 256 vectors you ingest,
   103	pinned in the workspace, and not silently recomputed thereafter.
   104	
   105	A consequence worth knowing: if the **first 256 documents** you ingest are not
   106	representative of the rest of your corpus (for example, you load one topic
   107	first and pivot later), the pinned mean can be skewed and retrieval quality may
   108	suffer. The remedy is to reindex; an automatic reindex/refresh path is planned
   109	for a later release.
   110	
   111	## Caveats and limitations
   112	
   113	- **Recall — corrected in 0.7.2.** Dev-box scouting during 0.7.1 measured
   114	  recall@10 around 0.83 over the reference corpus, which looked like it was below
   115	  the 0.90 floor. The 0.7.2 hardening work showed that 0.83 was a **measurement
   116	  artifact** (exclude-after-top-10 plus body-string ground truth over a corpus
   117	  with duplicate bodies), not an engine deficiency. The corrected ANN-fidelity
   118	  measurement — how faithfully the 1-bit sign-quant index reproduces the same
   119	  model's exact f32 top-10 — is **recall@10 = 0.937** (95% CI 0.913–0.957) on the
   120	  real bge-small embedder (N=7,667, K=192, mean-centering), so the **0.90 floor
   121	  holds**. This is an ANN/quantization-fidelity number, not an IR-relevance
   122	  number. A full-scale N=1M run remains infeasible on commodity hardware; 0.937
   123	  at N≈7.7k is treated as a near-upper bound (recall declines slowly with N).
   124	- **Topic-drift mean** (see above): pinned on the first 256 docs; reindex to
   125	  refresh.
   126	- **Custom Python/TypeScript embedders** are deferred to a later release; the
   127	  0.7.1 binding surface is binary (default-on or none).
   128	
   129	## Upgrading an existing workspace
   130	
   131	A workspace that was previously opened **without** the default embedder recorded
   132	a `fathomdb-noop` embedder identity. Re-opening it with the default embedder
   133	fails closed with an identity mismatch — this is intentional: vector identity
   134	belongs to the embedder, and silently re-embedding under a new model would
   135	corrupt retrieval. To adopt the default embedder on existing data, create a
   136	fresh workspace and re-ingest (wipe-and-rewrite). There is no in-place swap.
   137	
   138	## See also
   139	
   140	- `OpenReport` fields: [Python](install/python.md), [TypeScript](install/typescript.md)
   141	- Vector identity rationale: [Embedder Identity](positions/embedder-identity.md)

