dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PVQ-P2-RED-20260527T144439Z.log:194:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MQitMar9xuQvGP3S6Wv2zA","type":"tool_result","content":"189\t- **AC-013 latency budget re-pin** in\n190\t  `tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150`:\n191\t  - `AC013_BUDGET_P50 = Duration::from_millis(80);`\n192\t  - `AC013_BUDGET_P99 = Duration::from_millis(300);`\n193\t- **New AC recall-floor test** (e.g., `ac_NNN_recall_at_10`):\n194\t  - Computes brute-force f32 ground truth at test-setup\n195\t    (one pass through the existing f32 column, no\n196\t    rerank).\n197\t  - Runs the production search path, captures top-10 IDs\n198\t    per query.\n199\t  - Asserts `recall@10 ≥ 0.90` (HITL-locked floor).\n200\t  - The ground-truth pass uses the *same* f32 column that\n201\t    Pack 2 retains for rerank — single corpus, both jobs.\n202\t\n203\tBoth tests must FAIL at canonical-CI N=1M before the query\n204\trewrite lands. Dispatch the perf-canonical workflow with\n205\t`targets=\"ac013 ac019\"` and the locked W4.1-stacked-O1 env\n206\tknobs (see HITL doc) to confirm RED.\n207\t\n208\t### 2.2 — `read_search_in_tx` rewrite\n209\t\n210\tAt `lib.rs:2317-2323`, replace the single-phase f32 KNN with\n211\ttwo-phase:\n212\t\n213\t```sql\n214\t-- Phase 1: bit-KNN to top-K candidates (K=64 default)\n215\tWITH candidates AS (\n216\t  SELECT rowid, distance AS bit_distance\n217\t  FROM vector_default\n218\t  WHERE embedding_bin MATCH vec_quantize_binary(vec_f32(?1))\n219\t  ORDER BY distance\n220\t  LIMIT 64\n221\t)\n222\t-- Phase 2: f32 rerank on the candidate set\n223\tSELECT c.rowid, vec_distance_l2(v.embedding, vec_f32(?1)) AS d\n224\tFROM candidates c\n225\tJOIN vector_default v USING (rowid)\n226\tORDER BY d\n227\tLIMIT 10\n228\t```\n229\t\n230\t(Exact SQL TBD against sqlite-vec syntax — see\n231\t[sqlite-vec API ref](https://deepwiki.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/3-api-reference)\n232\tand the binary-quant guide cited in the research doc.)\n233\t\n234\tK=64 picked from the binary-quant literature (Cohere, Kyle\n235\tHowells benches) for ≥ 95 % recall@10 at our scale. Make K a\n236\tconstant / config knob so future tuning is cheap.\n237\t\n238\t### 2.3 — Pack 2 validation\n239\t\n240\t- Local dev-box smoke at N=10_000 — both tests pass.\n241\t- Canonical-CI dispatch with the same lever stack:\n242\t  - AC-013 GREEN at ≤ 80 / 300 ms.\n243\t  - AC-019 GREEN (existing 10× bound; should improve\n244\t    substantially).\n245\t  - Recall@10 ≥ 0.90 against f32 ground truth.\n246\t\n247\t### 2.4 — Pack 2 closure\n248\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"878701b8-da54-4911-aa70-258c930a87b2","uuid":"96d067db-79a4-435d-a3e7-a3ecb4966c23","timestamp":"2026-05-27T14:45:32.970Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P2-RED-20260527T144439Z/dev/plans/prompts/0.7.0-PERF-VECTOR-QUANT-HANDOFF.md","content":"- **AC-013 latency budget re-pin** in\n  `tests/perf_gates.rs:149-150`:\n  - `AC013_BUDGET_P50 = Duration::from_millis(80);`\n  - `AC013_BUDGET_P99 = Duration::from_millis(300);`\n- **New AC recall-floor test** (e.g., `ac_NNN_recall_at_10`):\n  - Computes brute-force f32 ground truth at test-setup\n    (one pass through the existing f32 column, no\n    rerank).\n  - Runs the production search path, captures top-10 IDs\n    per query.\n  - Asserts `recall@10 ≥ 0.90` (HITL-locked floor).\n  - The ground-truth pass uses the *same* f32 column that\n    Pack 2 retains for rerank — single corpus, both jobs.\n\nBoth tests must FAIL at canonical-CI N=1M before the query\nrewrite lands. Dispatch the perf-canonical workflow with\n`targets=\"ac013 ac019\"` and the locked W4.1-stacked-O1 env\nknobs (see HITL doc) to confirm RED.\n\n### 2.2 — `read_search_in_tx` rewrite\n\nAt `lib.rs:2317-2323`, replace the single-phase f32 KNN with\ntwo-phase:\n\n```sql\n-- Phase 1: bit-KNN to top-K candidates (K=64 default)\nWITH candidates AS (\n  SELECT rowid, distance AS bit_distance\n  FROM vector_default\n  WHERE embedding_bin MATCH vec_quantize_binary(vec_f32(?1))\n  ORDER BY distance\n  LIMIT 64\n)\n-- Phase 2: f32 rerank on the candidate set\nSELECT c.rowid, vec_distance_l2(v.embedding, vec_f32(?1)) AS d\nFROM candidates c\nJOIN vector_default v USING (rowid)\nORDER BY d\nLIMIT 10\n```\n\n(Exact SQL TBD against sqlite-vec syntax — see\n[sqlite-vec API ref](https://deepwiki.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/3-api-reference)\nand the binary-quant guide cited in the research doc.)\n\nK=64 picked from the binary-quant literature (Cohere, Kyle\nHowells benches) for ≥ 95 % recall@10 at our scale. Make K a\nconstant / config knob so future tuning is cheap.\n\n### 2.3 — Pack 2 validation\n\n- Local dev-box smoke at N=10_000 — both tests pass.\n- Canonical-CI dispatch with the same lever stack:\n  - AC-013 GREEN at ≤ 80 / 300 ms.\n  - AC-019 GREEN (existing 10× bound; should improve\n    substantially).\n  - Recall@10 ≥ 0.90 against f32 ground truth.\n\n### 2.4 — Pack 2 closure\n","numLines":60,"startLine":189,"totalLines":312}}}
