ted an 'operational_mutations' schema stamp instead of using the real migration framework.\",\n      \"remediation\": \"D4 rewritten: migration uses migrate_with_event_sink(...) at src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1238 gated by PRAGMA user_version. Schema rebuild is DROP TABLE + CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE under the same name (no rename). Repopulation reuses the existing Engine::rebuild_vec0 path (lib.rs:1947) which dispatches to rebuild_shadow_state with RebuildKind::Vec0 (lib.rs:2234-2289). Fabricated operational_mutations stamp removed. Cost baseline cites AC-013 562s seed time from dev/plans/runs/0.7.0-PERF-EXP-W4.1-ac013-canonical-output.json as an upper bound (rebuild skips embedder).\",\n      \"anchors\": [\n        \"dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md D4\",\n        \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1238\",\n        \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1947\",\n        \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2234-2289\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"finding\": 3,\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"summary\": \"D6 secondary normalise([1,-1,1,-1,...]) fixture incorrectly claimed identical sign pattern to the half/half fixture.\",\n      \"remediation\": \"Secondary fixture deleted. Half/half popcount=384 fixture retained as the sole RED-test fixture. Optional defence-in-depth fixture documented (v[i] = +1.0 if i % 4 == 0 else -1.0, popcount = 192) with explicit, hand-computable popcount.\",\n      \"anchors\": [\n        \"dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md D6\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"constraints_honored\": {\n    \"additive_commit_on_top_of_14a4612\": true,\n    \"no_code_changes\": true,\n    \"no_adr_edits\": true,\n    \"ascii_only\": true,\n    \"did_not_push\": true,\n    \"cited_real_migration_framework_anchors\": true\n  },\n  \"next_step_for_orchestrator\": \"re-spawn codex reviewer for fix-1 verdict\"\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
